examples: The one to the east—called the Uncharactered Tablet—is more than 6 meters high and was originally left blank under Wu Zetian's will, as she wanted later generations to evaluate her life  […]
In the summer a wretched uncharactered itinerant derives a scanty and precarious existence by wandering from parish to parish, and opening a school in some ditch covered with heath and furze,  […]
